    <stitle>GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - OPERATION - VOLTMETER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0803512" svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>VOLTMETER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The Speedo/Tach module monitors voltage levels in the feed circuit to the module.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Voltmeter Gauge</title>
            <para>The Speedo/Tach module monitors system voltage and outputs signals to drive the voltmeter, through
                connector (422) on circuits 27S(+), 27S(-), 27C(+) and 27C(-) to the left gauge cluster at connector
                (424). The voltmeter is a 4-pin electronically driven gauge that plugs into the gauge cluster.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
